+getpackages([{packname} [, {packtype} [, {plugname} [, {nameonly}]]]])
+		Return a List of package/plugin directories.
+
+		{packname} specifies a package name.  If it is not given or an
+		empty string, "*" is used.  |wildcards| can be used.
+		{packtype} specifies a package type.  It can be "opt", "start",
+		"*" or "NONE".  If it is not given or an empty string, "*" is
+		used.  If "NONE" is specified only package directories are
+		listed.  Otherwise all plugin directories under the specified
+		packages are listed.
+		{plugname} specifies a plugin name.  If it is not given or an
+		empty string, "*" is used.  |wildcards| can be used.
+		If {nameonly} is |TRUE|, plugin (or package) names are listed
+		instead of the directories.
+		See: |packages|
+
